<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>CodeSphere Competitive Programming</title>
    <script src="https://kit.fontawesome.com/a076d05399.js" crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: 'Poppins', sans-serif;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            background: #0f172a;
            color: white;
        }

        /* Navbar */
        .navbar {
            display: flex;
            justify-content: space-between;
            align-items: center;
            background: #1e3a8a;
            padding: 1rem 2rem;
            position: fixed;
            top: 0;
            width: 100%;
            z-index: 1000;
            box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
        }

        .navbar h1 {
            font-size: 1.5rem;
            margin: 0;
            color: #93c5fd;
        }

        .menu-icon {
            right: 40px;
            font-size: 1.8rem;
            cursor: pointer;
            color: white;
            position: relative;
            padding: 10px;
            background: #3b82f6;
            border-radius: 31px;
            transition: background 0.3s ease-in-out;
            z-index: 1100;
        }

        .menu-icon:hover {
            background: #2563eb;
        }

        .dropdown {
            display: none;
            position: absolute;
            top: 94px;
            right: 73px;
            background: #172554;
            border-radius: 8px;
            box-shadow: 0 2px 5px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);
            width: 200px;
            padding: 0;
            z-index: 1000;
        }

        .dropdown a {
            display: block;
            padding: 12px 16px;
            text-decoration: none;
            color: #93c5fd;
            font-weight: bold;
            transition: background 0.3s, color 0.3s;
        }

        .dropdown a:hover {
            background: #3b82f6;
            color: white;
        }

        .dropdown.active {
            display: block;
        }

        .container {
            display: flex;
            margin-top: 80px;
        }

        .sidebar {
            width: 250px;
            background: #172554;
            padding: 1rem;
            height: 100vh;
            overflow-y: auto;
            border-right: 2px solid #3b82f6;
            position: fixed;
            transition: 0.3s;
        }

        .sidebar h3 {
            color: #93c5fd;
            text-align: center;
            margin-bottom: 1rem;
        }

        .sidebar a {
            display: block;
            padding: 10px;
            margin-bottom: 8px;
            text-decoration: none;
            color: #93c5fd;
            font-weight: bold;
            border-radius: 5px;
            transition: 0.3s;
            text-align: center;
        }

        .sidebar a:hover {
            background: #3b82f6;
            color: white;
        }

        .content {
            flex-grow: 1;
            padding: 2rem;
            margin-left: 260px;
            transition: 0.3s;
        }

        h2 {
            color: #93c5fd;
            text-align: center;
        }

        .topic-section {
            margin-bottom: 2rem;
            padding: 1.5rem;
            background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
            border-radius: 8px;
            box-shadow: 0 2px 5px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
        }

        .topic-section h3 {
            color: #3b82f6;
            margin-bottom: 1rem;
        }

        .topic-section p {
            line-height: 1.6;
        }

        .topic-section ul {
            list-style-type: none;
            padding: 0;
        }

        .topic-section ul li {
            background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.05);
            margin: 8px 0;
            padding: 10px;
            border-radius: 5px;
            transition: background 0.3s;
        }

        .topic-section ul li:hover {
            background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
        }

        /* Responsive Styles */
        @media (max-width: 768px) {
            .container {
                flex-direction: column;
            }
            .sidebar {
                width: 100%;
                height: auto;
                position: relative;
                border-right: none;
                text-align: center;
                display: none;
            }
            .content {
                margin-left: 0;
                width: 100%;
            }
            .sidebar.active {
                display: block;
            }
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <!-- Navbar -->
    <div class="navbar">
        <h1>CodeSphere Competitive Programming</h1>
        <div class="menu-icon" onclick="toggleMenu()">â˜°</div>
        <div class="dropdown" id="dropdown-menu">
            <a href="/codesphere">Home</a>
            <a href="/profile">Profile</a>
            <a href="/ide">IDE</a>
            <a href="/cp2">Progress</a>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Main Container -->
    <div class="container">
        <!-- Sidebar -->
        <div class="sidebar" id="sidebar">
            <h3>Topics</h3>
            <a href="#introduction">Introduction</a>
            <a href="#data-structures">Data Structures</a>
            <a href="#algorithms">Algorithms</a>
            <a href="#problem-solving">Problem Solving</a>
            <a href="#online-judges">Online Judges</a>
            <a href="#resources">Resources</a>
            <a href="#practice-problems">Practice Problems</a>
            <a href="#contests">Contests</a>
        </div>

        <!-- Content -->
        <div class="content">
            <h2>Welcome to Competitive Programming</h2>

            <!-- Introduction -->
            <div id="introduction" class="topic-section">
                <h3>Introduction</h3>
                <p>Competitive programming is a mind sport where participants solve algorithmic problems under time constraints. It helps improve problem-solving skills and coding efficiency.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>What is Competitive Programming?</li>
                    <li>Why Participate in Competitive Programming?</li>
                    <li>Getting Started with Competitive Programming</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <!-- Data Structures -->
            <div id="data-structures" class="topic-section">
                <h3>Data Structures</h3>
                <p>Data structures are essential for organizing and managing data efficiently. Common data structures used in competitive programming include:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Arrays</li>
                    <li>Linked Lists</li>
                    <li>Stacks and Queues</li>
                    <li>Trees (Binary Trees, BST, AVL Trees)</li>
                    <li>Graphs</li>
                    <li>Hash Tables</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <!-- Algorithms -->
            <div id="algorithms" class="topic-section">
                <h3>Algorithms</h3>
                <p>Algorithms are step-by-step procedures for solving problems. Key algorithms for competitive programming include:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Sorting Algorithms (Quick Sort, Merge Sort)</li>
                    <li>Searching Algorithms (Binary Search)</li>
                    <li>Dynamic Programming</li>
                    <li>Greedy Algorithms</li>
                    <li>Graph Algorithms (BFS, DFS, Dijkstra's)</li>
                    <li>Number Theory Algorithms</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <!-- Problem Solving -->
            <div id="problem-solving" class="topic-section">
                <h3>Problem Solving</h3>
                <p>Problem-solving skills are crucial for competitive programming. Learn how to approach and solve problems efficiently.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Understanding Problem Statements</li>
                    <li>Breaking Down Problems</li>
                    <li>Time and Space Complexity Analysis</li>
                    <li>Optimizing Solutions</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <!-- Online Judges -->
            <div id="online-judges" class="topic-section">
                <h3>Online Judges</h3>
                <p>Online judges are platforms where you can practice and compete in programming challenges. Popular platforms include:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Codeforces</li>
                    <li>LeetCode</li>
                    <li>HackerRank</li>
                    <li>AtCoder</li>
                    <li>CodeChef</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <!-- Resources -->
            <div id="resources" class="topic-section">
                <h3>Resources</h3>
                <p>Here are some resources to help you learn and practice competitive programming:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Books: "Competitive Programming" by Steven Halim</li>
                    <li>Websites: GeeksforGeeks, CP-Algorithms</li>
                    <li>YouTube Channels: Errichto, William Lin</li>
                    <li>Practice Platforms: Codeforces, LeetCode</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <!-- Practice Problems -->
            <div id="practice-problems" class="topic-section">
                <h3>Practice Problems</h3>
                <p>Practice is key to mastering competitive programming. Solve problems from various categories:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Arrays and Strings</li>
                    <li>Dynamic Programming</li>
                    <li>Graph Theory</li>
                    <li>Number Theory</li>
                    <li>Greedy Algorithms</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <!-- Contests -->
            <div id="contests" class="topic-section">
                <h3>Contests</h3>
                <p>Participate in programming contests to test your skills and compete with others:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Codeforces Rounds</li>
                    <li>LeetCode Weekly Contests</li>
                    <li>Google Code Jam</li>
                    <li>ACM ICPC</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Script for Toggle Menu -->
    <script>
        function toggleMenu() {
            const dropdownMenu = document.getElementById("dropdown-menu");
            dropdownMenu.classList.toggle("active");
            const sidebar = document.getElementById("sidebar");
            sidebar.classList.toggle("active");
        }
    </script>

</body>
</html>